01Pick your destination

{/* Moon */}

Moon

See our planet as you've never seen it before. A perfect relaxing trip away to help regain perspective and come back refreshed. While you're there, take in some history by visiting the Luna 2 and Apollo 11 landing sites.

Avg. distance

384,400 km

Est. travel time

3 days

{/* Mars */}

Mars

Don't forget to pack your hiking boots. You'll need them to tackle Olympus Mons, the tallest planetary mountain in our solar system. It's two and half times the size of Mount Everest!

Avg. distance

225 mil. km

Est. travel time

9 months

{/* Europa */}

Europa

The smallest of the four Galilean moons orbiting Jupiter, Europa is a winter lover's dream. With an icy surface, it's perfect for a bit of ice skating, curling, hocket, or simple relaxation in your snnug wintery cabin.

Avg. distance

628 mil. km

Est. travel time

3 years

{/* Titan */}

Titan

The only moon known to have a dense atmosphere other than the planet Earth, Titan is a home away from home (just a few hundred degrees coler!). As a bonus you get striking views of the Rings of Saturn.

Avg. distance

1.6 bil. km

Est. travel time

7 years
